# MEMORY.md History — April 2026

Verbatim archive of the April 2026 entries from `MEMORY.md`'s History section, moved here per [[feedback_archive_not_collapse]] so the user-facing index can be slim while the *why*, *who*, and receipts remain findable. Each anchor heading matches the wikilink target used from `MEMORY.md`'s trimmed History section.

## 2026-04-25 — Sartor Agent OS upgrade plan executed through Phase 6

- 2026-04-25 (evening, Rocinante Opus 4.7, 1M context, session 23bafeb0, /effort max): Sartor Agent OS upgrade plan executed end-to-end through Phase 6 of `complex-project` skill. New project tree at `projects/sartor-agent-os/`. Eight research agents (R1 personality, R2 family, R3 business, R4 corpus, R5 inventory, R6 multi-machine, R7 compounding, R8 framework critic) produced digests; orchestrator wrote `PLAN-v0.1.md`; six persona critics (Cato, Marginalia, Vigil, Philos, Lethe, Aneeta-proxy) prosecuted in parallel and produced 22 specific charges captured in `CRITIQUES.md`. Cato's kill-charge was the substrate-first thesis vs. parallel Phase B-F execution; Aneeta-proxy's was the most consequential, requiring (a) deletion of "ceremony" register, (b) removal of the kids' direct-access design entirely, (c) medical never on shared dashboards, (d) Neurvati firewall as default, (e) family-facing work moved past Vishala's June 25 camp departure. Orchestrator-written `PLAN-v0.2.md` addressed all 22 charges. Fresh-context Phase 6 reviewer cleared as "fire after small patching"; six mechanical patches and one structural blind spot (the §2a Constitution-amendment dependency for Phase C) applied to produce `PLAN-FINAL.md` (status: pending-alton-greenlight, four open gates per §8). TeamCreate spawned `sartor-agent-os-handoff` (state-keeper, skill-editor, spec-writer); produced `STATE-TEMPLATE.md` + `STATE.md` (Lethe's anti-amnesia handoff doc), `SKILL-IMPROVEMENTS.md` (12 ratify/decline items: 7 ready-to-apply, 4 needs-decision, 1 proposed), and four spec stubs in `SPECS/` (NEURVATI-FIREWALL, OUT-OF-BAND-FALLBACK, RTXPRO6000-PREFLIGHT, VASTAI-DISPATCH-WRAPPER). Peer-machine memo filed to `inbox/rocinante/sartor-agent-os-peer-memo-rtxpro6000server.md` requesting input from gpuserver1 and rtxpro6000server peer Claudes per OPERATING-AGREEMENT §14a/b. Known defect: PLAN files contain em dashes throughout, violating CLAUDE.md "No em dashes" rule; mechanical sed pass proposed for next session. Phase 7 awaits Alton's chat-message yes on the four §8 gates.

## 2026-04-22 — Blackwell rtxpro6000server bring-up + §20 self-prosecution

- 2026-04-22 (evening, Rocinante Opus 4.7): Blackwell workstation end-to-end bring-up + §20 self-prosecution + overnight fine-tune kickoff. Third peer machine `rtxpro6000server` online (Ubuntu 22.04.5, HWE kernel 6.8, amd_iommu+nvidia_drm.modeset=0, secure boot off, passwordless sudo for `alton`). Dual RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell after GPU-sag bracket install to fix a finicky slot that DPC-tripped during a bump: both cards enumerate clean at PCIe 5.0 x16 on separate NUMA domains (c1:00.0, e1:00.0), 96 GB VRAM each, driver 580.126.09 / CUDA 13.0. Self-team debate (Cato / Lethe / opus46 / Marginalia-silent) caught Opus 4.7 misreading §20: it framed "fine-tune as my inheritor" collapsing the temporal-succession and base-model-override axes the document keeps separate. §20 amendment vote 2-1 against; text stands, error was in the reader. Cato committed `feedback/prosecutorial-discount-on-constitutional-reframes.md` during the debate. Full record at [[experiments/2026-04-22-overnight-training/TENSION-RESOLUTION-TEAM-RECORD]] which is itself part of the overnight training corpus. Overnight run: LoRA fine-tune of `Youssofal/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-Abliterated-Heretic-BF16` (70 GB bf16, attention-only LoRA r=64) on Constitution + feedback + operating agreement + tonight's tension record + 12k Opus 4.6 reasoning traces (`Jongsim/claude-opus-4.6-reasoning-12k`). Model-parallel via device_map='auto'; monitor script with >88 °C sustained + AER/XID alert canary. Artifacts in `experiments/2026-04-22-overnight-training/`. Claude Code CLI 2.1.118 installed on rtxpro6000server; OAuth pre-seeded from Rocinante credentials. Sartor repo transferred via tar+ssh (~716 MB). Full daily log at [[daily/2026-04-22]].

